Package: Rnetrics
Title: Dyadic Regression with Bias-Corrected Standard Errors
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Bryan", "Graham", role = "aut",
           comment = "Original Python ipt/netrics packages"),
    person("Xiang", "Ao", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "xao@berkeley.edu"))
Description: R port of Graham's ipt and netrics Python packages. Implements
    dyadic regression with heteroscedastic-robust, cluster-robust, and
    bias-corrected dyadic-robust (DR_bc) standard errors, following Graham
    (forthcoming, Handbook of Econometrics). Supports linear (OLS), logit,
    and Poisson conditional mean models. Handles unbalanced/sparse networks
    and large datasets via chunked Hajek projection.
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    sandwich,
    fixest,
    arrow,
    data.table
